1
00:00:17,500 --> 00:00:18,833
And then,

2
00:00:18,916 --> 00:00:21,041
the woman led the policeman
through the dark hallways

3
00:00:21,125 --> 00:00:23,416
to the public restroom
in the back.

4
00:00:23,500 --> 00:00:26,375
Once there, the policeman
told her to go back inside

5
00:00:26,458 --> 00:00:28,708
and wait to see if she
could hear the voice again,

6
00:00:28,791 --> 00:00:31,208
and she did just
as she was told.

7
00:00:31,291 --> 00:00:33,583
Do you want me to cover
you with a red coat?

8
00:00:33,666 --> 00:00:35,458
She answered...

9
00:00:35,541 --> 00:00:36,458
Yes.

10
00:00:36,541 --> 00:00:37,708
And then!

11
00:00:41,291 --> 00:00:43,208
The policeman burst
through the door

12
00:00:43,291 --> 00:00:45,916
and found the girl
totally covered in blood,

13
00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:48,708
as if she had a red
coat draped over her.

14
00:00:48,791 --> 00:00:49,875
Mai you know we hate it

15
00:00:49,958 --> 00:00:52,000
when you use that
creepy voice!

16
00:00:52,083 --> 00:00:53,291
That day was
like any other,

17
00:00:53,375 --> 00:00:55,666
staying late after school
telling ghost stories.

18
00:00:55,750 --> 00:00:57,958
Every time we finish a
story we turn off a light,

19
00:00:58,041 --> 00:00:59,500
and then, once
we're all done,

20
00:00:59,583 --> 00:01:01,333
there's always
one light left,

21
00:01:01,416 --> 00:01:03,041
meaning there's another
person in the room.

22
00:01:03,125 --> 00:01:05,125
You're up next, Michiru.

23
00:01:05,208 --> 00:01:07,708
The other person is
supposedly a ghost!

24
00:01:07,791 --> 00:01:10,041
Okay. This one's about
the old schoolhouse.

25
00:01:10,125 --> 00:01:11,666
Do you mean that
creepy old building

26
00:01:11,750 --> 00:01:13,625
down the street
that's collapsing?

27
00:01:13,708 --> 00:01:15,500
But it's not collapsing...

28
00:01:15,583 --> 00:01:18,250
It was being demolished when
the workers suddenly quit.

29
00:01:18,333 --> 00:01:19,458
Because of a curse.

30
00:01:21,041 --> 00:01:23,333
Lots of people have died in that
schoolhouse over the years,

31
00:01:23,416 --> 00:01:26,416
most famously a teacher
that committed suicide.

32
00:01:26,500 --> 00:01:29,000
So when they decided to
build the new school

33
00:01:29,083 --> 00:01:32,333
they started to tear
down the old one,

34
00:01:32,416 --> 00:01:33,333
but then...

35
00:01:37,583 --> 00:01:41,000
The demolition
ended that day.

36
00:01:41,083 --> 00:01:42,791
Last year they started
the demolition again

37
00:01:42,875 --> 00:01:44,583
to make way for
a new gymnasium

38
00:01:44,666 --> 00:01:46,541
but a truck driving
by lost control

39
00:01:46,625 --> 00:01:48,666
and crashed into a
group of kids outside,

40
00:01:48,750 --> 00:01:50,708
killing some students.

41
00:01:50,791 --> 00:01:52,125
But there's more...

42
00:01:52,208 --> 00:01:55,291
I heard about this
from an upperclassman.

43
00:01:55,375 --> 00:01:58,041
One night a student was
walking past the old school

44
00:01:58,125 --> 00:01:59,166
when...

45
00:02:06,958 --> 00:02:08,333
Here goes.

46
00:02:08,416 --> 00:02:12,250
One. Two. Three. Four.

47
00:02:14,458 --> 00:02:16,041
It's the ghost!
It's here to murder us!

48
00:02:18,291 --> 00:02:21,000
Oh, Please tell me
that was you just now!

49
00:02:21,083 --> 00:02:22,333
Am I interrupting?

50
00:02:24,625 --> 00:02:26,250
I thought for sure
it was the ghost.

51
00:02:26,333 --> 00:02:28,916
Sorry I didn't expect
anyone to be here.

52
00:02:29,000 --> 00:02:29,958
But then I heard
your voices

53
00:02:30,041 --> 00:02:31,416
and couldn't
help myself.

54
00:02:34,250 --> 00:02:36,333
Oh no... It's totally fine!

55
00:02:37,750 --> 00:02:39,000
What year are you?

56
00:02:39,083 --> 00:02:40,541
I'm seventeen this year.

57
00:02:41,875 --> 00:02:45,125
Normally someone would
just say they're a senior.

58
00:02:45,208 --> 00:02:47,375
So we were just
telling ghost stories.

59
00:02:47,458 --> 00:02:48,583
I see...

60
00:02:48,666 --> 00:02:50,375
Well maybe I could
join you guys sometime.

61
00:02:50,458 --> 00:02:53,166
Wow... Do you mean you like
telling ghost stories too?

62
00:02:53,250 --> 00:02:55,291
Yeah...

63
00:02:55,375 --> 00:02:56,875
You seem like a
really cool guy.

64
00:02:56,958 --> 00:02:58,458
What's your name?

65
00:02:58,541 --> 00:03:00,083
My name is Kazuya.

66
00:03:00,166 --> 00:03:01,625
His eyes.

67
00:03:01,708 --> 00:03:03,416
They're not smiling.

68
00:03:03,500 --> 00:03:04,708
Okay Kazuya...

69
00:03:04,791 --> 00:03:06,208
I have one question ...

70
00:03:06,291 --> 00:03:07,541
Why are you here?

71
00:03:07,625 --> 00:03:09,208
There are some things
I need to take care of.

72
00:03:09,291 --> 00:03:11,666
What're you
waiting for...?

73
00:03:11,750 --> 00:03:13,166
Do you need our
help for anything?

74
00:03:13,250 --> 00:03:15,291
No... but I would
love to be invited

75
00:03:15,375 --> 00:03:17,166
to join you the next time
you tell Ghost Stories.

76
00:03:17,250 --> 00:03:19,166
Of course!
You're welcome anytime!

77
00:03:19,250 --> 00:03:20,958
How about tomorrow?
After school?

78
00:03:21,041 --> 00:03:22,500
Okay... But Where?

79
00:03:22,583 --> 00:03:24,875
Right here.

80
00:03:24,958 --> 00:03:26,791
Something's
fishy about him.

81
00:03:26,875 --> 00:03:28,708
I better get to
the bottom of this!

82
00:03:30,166 --> 00:03:36,125
[Music]

83
00:05:06,875 --> 00:05:08,708
I love this weather!

84
00:05:08,791 --> 00:05:11,333
And I'm so glad
I left early...

85
00:05:11,416 --> 00:05:13,458
I've got all the cherry
blossoms to myself!

86
00:05:24,750 --> 00:05:25,916
The more I look
at this place,

87
00:05:26,000 --> 00:05:28,083
the more I believe
the stories.

88
00:05:30,125 --> 00:05:31,083
What's that?

89
00:05:32,000 --> 00:05:33,500
A video camera?

90
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:43,833
But... What's it
doing here...?

91
00:05:43,916 --> 00:05:45,625
I thought this
place was abandoned.

92
00:05:45,708 --> 00:05:46,750
I doesn't make sense

93
00:05:46,833 --> 00:05:48,083
that someone would
just leave it here.

94
00:05:48,166 --> 00:05:49,916
Who's there?

95
00:05:50,000 --> 00:05:51,458
Uh... I'm sorry...

96
00:05:51,541 --> 00:05:52,583
I'll leave now.

97
00:05:54,083 --> 00:05:55,458
Oh no...! Help!

98
00:06:13,875 --> 00:06:15,125
Hey Mister, are you okay?!

99
00:06:16,333 --> 00:06:18,208
Oh no. What should I do? I...

100
00:06:18,291 --> 00:06:19,541
What's going on in here?

101
00:06:21,125 --> 00:06:22,875
It's that guy
from yesterday.

102
00:06:24,750 --> 00:06:26,125
Lin... What just happened?

103
00:06:28,666 --> 00:06:29,958
You're bleeding.

104
00:06:30,041 --> 00:06:31,541
-Can you stand?
-Yeah.

105
00:06:31,625 --> 00:06:32,666
Oh my gosh...

106
00:06:32,750 --> 00:06:34,291
I'm really sorry
about this.

107
00:06:34,375 --> 00:06:36,208
He startled me and I guess
I turned around too fast.

108
00:06:36,291 --> 00:06:37,708
Never mind all that...

109
00:06:37,791 --> 00:06:40,125
Is there a
doctor close by?

110
00:06:40,208 --> 00:06:42,083
There's a doctor just
down the street from here.

111
00:06:44,250 --> 00:06:45,333
No thanks...

112
00:06:45,416 --> 00:06:47,458
You've done enough
already as it is.

113
00:06:49,750 --> 00:06:50,708
But...

114
00:06:50,791 --> 00:06:51,791
We met yesterday, right...?

115
00:06:51,875 --> 00:06:52,833
What's your name?

116
00:06:52,916 --> 00:06:54,541
It's uh... Mai.

117
00:06:54,625 --> 00:06:56,166
Well alright then Mai...

118
00:06:56,250 --> 00:06:57,500
I thought you
might want to know

119
00:06:57,583 --> 00:06:58,916
that you're going to be
late for your first class

120
00:06:59,000 --> 00:07:00,375
since the morning
bell just rang.

121
00:07:03,166 --> 00:07:04,125
I'm late?

122
00:07:04,208 --> 00:07:05,750
I don't believe this!

123
00:07:05,833 --> 00:07:07,416
What the heck was
that all about?

124
00:07:07,500 --> 00:07:10,333
I never want to step foot
in that creepy place again!

125
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:15,583
Mai, are you leaving now?

126
00:07:15,666 --> 00:07:16,916
We're supposed to
tell ghost stories

127
00:07:17,000 --> 00:07:19,541
-with that cute guy, remember?
-Not me.

128
00:07:19,625 --> 00:07:21,500
Awe, come on, Mai. Please!

129
00:07:21,583 --> 00:07:23,958
This is our chance to tell
ghost stories with a senior!

130
00:07:24,041 --> 00:07:25,791
Did you say ghost stories?

131
00:07:25,875 --> 00:07:29,666
Is that what you three do
after school every day?

132
00:07:29,750 --> 00:07:32,291
Then no wonder I've had
this headache for so long...

133
00:07:32,375 --> 00:07:34,375
I'm very attuned
to spirits...

134
00:07:34,458 --> 00:07:36,375
When they gather in
groups I get headaches.

135
00:07:36,458 --> 00:07:38,791
So you're...
blaming us for that?

136
00:07:38,875 --> 00:07:40,208
Of course I am.

137
00:07:40,291 --> 00:07:42,208
Whenever you tell one of
your little ghost stories

138
00:07:42,291 --> 00:07:43,708
you attract low
level spirits,

139
00:07:43,791 --> 00:07:45,208
and they attract
stronger spirits...

140
00:07:45,291 --> 00:07:47,166
and then we're
in big trouble.

141
00:07:47,250 --> 00:07:49,125
So when you entertain
yourselves with these stories

142
00:07:49,208 --> 00:07:50,625
you're putting me at risk.

143
00:07:50,708 --> 00:07:52,250
So tell me...

144
00:07:52,333 --> 00:07:54,250
If you're sensitive to
spirits like you claim

145
00:07:54,333 --> 00:07:57,125
then do you sense anything
with the old schoolhouse?

146
00:07:57,208 --> 00:07:59,375
Oh my gosh Kazuya
came to find us!

147
00:07:59,458 --> 00:08:00,458
Hold on...

148
00:08:00,541 --> 00:08:01,708
Are you the one
who put these girls

149
00:08:01,791 --> 00:08:04,458
up to telling these
ridiculous ghost stories?

150
00:08:04,541 --> 00:08:06,791
You didn't answer
my question.

151
00:08:06,875 --> 00:08:09,541
Could it be your psychic
abilities are made up?

152
00:08:09,625 --> 00:08:12,375
For your information there are
numerous spirits of those

153
00:08:12,458 --> 00:08:15,083
who died in the war that
gather in the old schoolhouse.

154
00:08:15,166 --> 00:08:16,583
In fact, I'm positive

155
00:08:16,666 --> 00:08:19,208
that building was used as a
hospital during the war.

156
00:08:19,291 --> 00:08:21,541
I've just seen too many
injured spirits there.

157
00:08:23,291 --> 00:08:25,958
I was not aware of a hospital
being here during the war...

158
00:08:26,041 --> 00:08:28,375
I know this school was
founded well before the war

159
00:08:28,458 --> 00:08:31,791
so maybe... this was
a medical school?

160
00:08:31,875 --> 00:08:33,291
Look I don't know.

161
00:08:33,375 --> 00:08:35,250
But I really do
see spirits...

162
00:08:35,333 --> 00:08:37,458
If you're not psychic
you wouldn't understand.

163
00:08:37,541 --> 00:08:39,375
Sorry Kazuya...

164
00:08:39,458 --> 00:08:41,166
Can we do this
some other time?

165
00:08:41,250 --> 00:08:43,416
Yeah I'm not in the
mood anymore either.

166
00:08:43,500 --> 00:08:45,666
No...? Perhaps another day.

167
00:08:47,583 --> 00:08:48,750
Oh, and Mai?

168
00:08:51,083 --> 00:08:52,625
Would you mind coming
with me for a moment?

169
00:08:59,125 --> 00:09:00,583
How's you friend doing?

170
00:09:00,666 --> 00:09:02,000
Yes about him.

171
00:09:02,083 --> 00:09:03,750
He suffered a sprain
to his left leg

172
00:09:03,833 --> 00:09:06,166
and I'm afraid he won't
be walking for awhile.

173
00:09:06,250 --> 00:09:08,250
Gosh. Will you please
tell him I'm sorry?

174
00:09:08,333 --> 00:09:10,875
So what were you two
doing there anyway?

175
00:09:10,958 --> 00:09:12,083
Working.

176
00:09:12,166 --> 00:09:13,750
Oh I get it.
You work for him.

177
00:09:13,833 --> 00:09:15,666
Are you like his
assistant or something?

178
00:09:15,750 --> 00:09:16,916
No, not quite.

179
00:09:18,458 --> 00:09:19,416
He's the assistant.

180
00:09:19,500 --> 00:09:21,666
I'm the boss.

181
00:09:21,750 --> 00:09:23,833
And now my assistant
is stuck in a bed...

182
00:09:23,916 --> 00:09:25,833
I believe it's up to
you to take his place.

183
00:09:25,916 --> 00:09:27,125
Hey now hold on
just a minute!

184
00:09:27,208 --> 00:09:29,666
The camera's broken.

185
00:09:29,750 --> 00:09:32,458
My assistant tried to stop
you from touching the camera...

186
00:09:32,541 --> 00:09:34,458
and it now it's
in several pieces.

187
00:09:34,541 --> 00:09:36,708
Well Uh Can't I just buy
you a new one or something?

188
00:09:36,791 --> 00:09:38,666
It's quite expensive.

189
00:09:38,750 --> 00:09:40,875
Oh, then I don't
know what to do.

190
00:09:40,958 --> 00:09:42,500
You can't afford
to reimburse me

191
00:09:42,583 --> 00:09:43,916
for the damaged equipment,

192
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:46,166
which means there's only one
other course we can take.

193
00:09:46,250 --> 00:09:48,458
You'll work off the
debt as my assistant.

194
00:09:48,541 --> 00:09:50,416
Your assis... tant...?

195
00:09:50,500 --> 00:09:53,583
You seriously think I should
start working for you?

196
00:09:53,666 --> 00:09:55,958
Well, that's what I said.

197
00:09:56,041 --> 00:09:57,625
What do you do
at your job?

198
00:09:57,708 --> 00:09:59,416
I hunt ghosts.

199
00:09:59,500 --> 00:10:00,750
Huh?

200
00:10:00,833 --> 00:10:03,416
In other words,
I exorcise spirits... ghosts...

201
00:10:03,500 --> 00:10:05,583
my company, Shibuya
Psychic Research

202
00:10:05,666 --> 00:10:07,250
was hired to conduct
an investigation

203
00:10:07,333 --> 00:10:08,625
on the old schoolhouse.

204
00:10:08,708 --> 00:10:10,416
Psychic research?

205
00:10:10,500 --> 00:10:11,708
Is that a question?

206
00:10:13,041 --> 00:10:14,875
Psychic research
is another term

207
00:10:14,958 --> 00:10:17,583
for spiritual investigations.

208
00:10:17,666 --> 00:10:19,708
We basically examine
and scrutinize reports

209
00:10:19,791 --> 00:10:21,208
of supernatural phenomena.

210
00:10:23,208 --> 00:10:24,458
And I run the company.

211
00:10:37,791 --> 00:10:39,166
Oh man!

212
00:10:39,250 --> 00:10:41,708
One week ago, your principal
contacted my company.

213
00:10:42,708 --> 00:10:43,916
Well the problem is...

214
00:10:44,000 --> 00:10:45,791
we constantly have to
run damage control

215
00:10:45,875 --> 00:10:48,125
over a rumor that the
schoolhouse is haunted.

216
00:10:48,208 --> 00:10:49,625
When I checked the records,

217
00:10:49,708 --> 00:10:52,166
I was able to verify that
up until eighteen years ago,

218
00:10:52,250 --> 00:10:54,416
while the old schoolhouse
was still being used,

219
00:10:54,500 --> 00:10:56,333
there would be at
least one or two deaths

220
00:10:56,416 --> 00:10:58,000
inside the structure
every year.

221
00:10:58,083 --> 00:11:00,041
It's also true that when
construction crews

222
00:11:00,125 --> 00:11:02,500
were demolishing the
east side of the building,

223
00:11:02,583 --> 00:11:05,291
there was an accident where
the roof collapsed prematurely.

224
00:11:05,375 --> 00:11:07,166
No workers died
as a result,

225
00:11:07,250 --> 00:11:08,833
though five were
injured in the incident,

226
00:11:08,916 --> 00:11:11,166
which was ultimately
blamed on human error.

227
00:11:11,250 --> 00:11:12,458
Construction ended

228
00:11:12,541 --> 00:11:14,208
with only a third of the
planned demolition work

229
00:11:14,291 --> 00:11:15,583
ever being finished...

230
00:11:15,666 --> 00:11:18,458
A teacher did in fact commit
suicide in the building,

231
00:11:18,541 --> 00:11:20,333
but that was explained
in the suicide note

232
00:11:20,416 --> 00:11:21,708
left by the victim.

233
00:11:21,791 --> 00:11:23,250
The incident with
the truck last year

234
00:11:23,333 --> 00:11:25,083
was a drunk
driving accident.

235
00:11:25,166 --> 00:11:27,625
That's when construction was
stopped for the last time.

236
00:11:27,708 --> 00:11:30,625
No doubt, the rumors played
a part in this decision.

237
00:11:30,708 --> 00:11:31,958
Based on my research,

238
00:11:32,041 --> 00:11:34,208
the existence of
paranormal activity here

239
00:11:34,291 --> 00:11:35,541
is nothing more
than fiction.

240
00:11:35,625 --> 00:11:37,041
For a place this
active as this,

241
00:11:37,125 --> 00:11:40,541
every occurrence has a
reasonable explanation.

242
00:11:40,625 --> 00:11:41,875
We'll set up base here.

243
00:11:41,958 --> 00:11:42,958
Base?

244
00:11:44,333 --> 00:11:46,500
Precisely...we'll conduct
all of our observations

245
00:11:46,583 --> 00:11:47,708
from this room.

246
00:11:47,791 --> 00:11:48,708
Oh yeah of course.

247
00:11:48,791 --> 00:11:50,291
Guess I'm still learning.

248
00:11:50,375 --> 00:11:52,000
Set up those
shelves for me.

249
00:11:52,083 --> 00:11:53,541
I'll start bringing
in equipment.

250
00:11:53,625 --> 00:11:55,625
You're gonna leave me
here all by myself?

251
00:11:55,708 --> 00:11:57,458
Would you rather carry
this stuff in...?

252
00:11:57,541 --> 00:12:00,125
It's heavy. Some of it's weighs
up to a hundred pounds.

253
00:12:00,208 --> 00:12:02,166
I'll stick to shelves.

254
00:12:02,250 --> 00:12:04,708
I can't believe how
stuck up this guy is!

255
00:12:04,791 --> 00:12:07,041
I mean, sure it was my fault
that his assistant got hurt,

256
00:12:07,125 --> 00:12:09,125
but does he have to
act so self- important?

257
00:12:27,083 --> 00:12:29,250
Stop goofing off
and get back to work.

258
00:12:30,666 --> 00:12:31,708
It's official.

259
00:12:31,791 --> 00:12:33,000
I hate him.

260
00:12:34,541 --> 00:12:35,791
What' are those?

261
00:12:35,875 --> 00:12:38,708
An infrared camera and a
thermal-imaging camera.

262
00:12:38,791 --> 00:12:40,750
They're used to shoot
in total darkness.

263
