327
00:15:14,166 --> 00:15:15,875
So far there seems to
be nothing unusual.

328
00:15:15,958 --> 00:15:18,083
That's some fancy
equipment you got there.

329
00:15:18,166 --> 00:15:20,416
It seems a bit too high tech
for a couple of children

330
00:15:20,500 --> 00:15:21,791
to be playing with.

331
00:15:23,416 --> 00:15:24,750
And who might you be?

332
00:15:24,833 --> 00:15:27,083
I am Ayako the
shrine maiden...

333
00:15:27,166 --> 00:15:28,333
The principal
wasn't sold on you

334
00:15:28,416 --> 00:15:30,625
so he called me to
drive the spirits out.

335
00:15:30,708 --> 00:15:32,041
I was under the impression

336
00:15:32,125 --> 00:15:34,500
that only innocent virgins
can become shrine maidens.

337
00:15:34,583 --> 00:15:36,625
I see... and... your point!

338
00:15:36,708 --> 00:15:38,916
At the very least I'd say
you're looking a little old

339
00:15:39,000 --> 00:15:40,291
to be calling
yourself a maiden.

340
00:15:40,375 --> 00:15:41,375
Nice...

341
00:15:41,458 --> 00:15:43,375
Very funny you
smart-ass...

342
00:15:43,458 --> 00:15:44,541
What about you?

343
00:15:44,625 --> 00:15:46,125
I would guess you're
too intelligent

344
00:15:46,208 --> 00:15:48,000
to be the shrine
maiden's assistant.

345
00:15:48,083 --> 00:15:49,666
I'm a monk from Mt. Koya.

346
00:15:49,750 --> 00:15:51,541
The name's Takigawa Hosho.

347
00:15:51,625 --> 00:15:53,875
Since when were monks
allowed to have long hair?

348
00:15:53,958 --> 00:15:55,041
Apostate?

349
00:15:55,125 --> 00:15:57,125
I'm just on a little
hiatus okay...?

350
00:15:57,208 --> 00:15:59,916
At any rate,
playtime is over kids.

351
00:16:00,000 --> 00:16:01,125
Now you may have
gotten this gig

352
00:16:01,208 --> 00:16:02,541
because your
office is nearby,

353
00:16:02,625 --> 00:16:04,083
but the principal
himself said

354
00:16:04,166 --> 00:16:06,583
it seemed like a scam to have
a teenager running the show.

355
00:16:06,666 --> 00:16:07,833
Did he now?

356
00:16:07,916 --> 00:16:09,416
The principal's
wasting his money...

357
00:16:09,500 --> 00:16:10,625
There's no need
to have all of us

358
00:16:10,708 --> 00:16:12,166
for such a simple job.

359
00:16:12,250 --> 00:16:14,125
Yeah... All he
really needed was me.

360
00:16:14,208 --> 00:16:16,583
Right... I wouldn't
be so sure.

361
00:16:16,666 --> 00:16:18,875
Oh thank goodness
you're all here.

362
00:16:18,958 --> 00:16:20,125
That haunted
old schoolhouse

363
00:16:20,208 --> 00:16:22,583
has been terrorizing
me for weeks.

364
00:16:22,666 --> 00:16:24,250
You see, I'm a psychic.

365
00:16:24,333 --> 00:16:25,875
The souls of those
trapped there have...

366
00:16:25,958 --> 00:16:27,541
Stop grandstanding...

367
00:16:27,625 --> 00:16:29,583
You're just looking
for attention.

368
00:16:29,666 --> 00:16:32,125
Are you really that desperate
for people to like you?

369
00:16:32,208 --> 00:16:34,208
Excuse me! That
was extremely rude!

370
00:16:34,291 --> 00:16:35,958
You know it's the truth.

371
00:16:36,041 --> 00:16:38,208
She claims to have psychic
abilities in the hopes

372
00:16:38,291 --> 00:16:39,750
that it will somehow
make her popular.

373
00:16:39,833 --> 00:16:41,458
That is totally
uncalled for!

374
00:16:43,500 --> 00:16:45,625
I'm gonna call a
spirit to haunt you.

375
00:16:46,791 --> 00:16:47,875
Hold on Kuroda.

376
00:16:47,958 --> 00:16:49,083
You're the fake...

377
00:16:49,166 --> 00:16:51,000
And you'll regret this.

378
00:16:52,666 --> 00:16:56,458
Whoa... I've never seen
her look so angry before.

379
00:16:56,541 --> 00:16:57,875
Hey Naru...

380
00:16:57,958 --> 00:16:59,541
So... What's up?

381
00:16:59,625 --> 00:17:01,041
What are we
gonna do today?

382
00:17:01,125 --> 00:17:03,625
Wait... What did you just say?

383
00:17:03,708 --> 00:17:05,583
Did you call me Naru?

384
00:17:05,666 --> 00:17:07,666
Sorry... I...

385
00:17:07,750 --> 00:17:08,791
Where did you hear that?

386
00:17:08,875 --> 00:17:10,208
Huh...? You mean...

387
00:17:10,291 --> 00:17:11,916
You've been called
that before?

388
00:17:12,000 --> 00:17:13,250
Of course, that
makes sense.

389
00:17:13,333 --> 00:17:14,916
I can't be the first to
think up something like

390
00:17:15,000 --> 00:17:16,333
Naru the Narcissist.

391
00:17:16,416 --> 00:17:18,541
Morning everyone.
Nice to see you all.

392
00:17:18,625 --> 00:17:20,833
Say hello to John Brown.

393
00:17:20,916 --> 00:17:22,125
G'day mates.

394
00:17:24,041 --> 00:17:25,291
The name's John Brown

395
00:17:25,375 --> 00:17:27,875
and I come from the great
outback of Australia...

396
00:17:27,958 --> 00:17:30,166
I can't express how
excited I am to join you.

397
00:17:30,250 --> 00:17:32,375
Mr. Brown is relatively
new to our country

398
00:17:32,458 --> 00:17:34,541
so please show him the
respect he deserves.

399
00:17:36,500 --> 00:17:38,541
Let me guess! You're looking
for a playground, right?

400
00:17:38,625 --> 00:17:42,791
Well... Actually I practice
the ancient art of exorcism.

401
00:17:42,875 --> 00:17:44,041
Only those who
have been ordained

402
00:17:44,125 --> 00:17:45,541
in the Catholic
church as priests

403
00:17:45,625 --> 00:17:47,500
have the ability to
conduct exorcisms...

404
00:17:47,583 --> 00:17:48,666
You seem young for that.

405
00:17:48,750 --> 00:17:50,166
You really know
your stuff mate.

406
00:17:50,250 --> 00:17:52,750
And to be honest I just turned
nineteen a few weeks ago,

407
00:17:52,833 --> 00:17:54,208
That's why I look so young.

408
00:17:54,291 --> 00:17:55,583
He's nineteen?

409
00:17:55,666 --> 00:17:57,250
That means he's
older than Naru.

410
00:17:57,333 --> 00:17:59,125
So we have an exorcist,
an apostate monk

411
00:17:59,208 --> 00:18:00,250
and a ghost hunter.

412
00:18:00,333 --> 00:18:01,916
Obviously this
bone-headed principal

413
00:18:02,000 --> 00:18:05,125
doesn't have much faith in my
unique cleansing abilities.

414
00:18:05,208 --> 00:18:06,208
Just watch.

415
00:18:06,291 --> 00:18:07,875
I'll clear this
entire place myself.

416
00:18:07,958 --> 00:18:09,250
I'm gonna do
a walkthrough.

417
00:18:09,333 --> 00:18:10,666
See you later.

418
00:18:10,750 --> 00:18:12,125
Uh, excuse me sir ...

419
00:18:12,208 --> 00:18:13,416
You may do as you wish.

420
00:18:13,500 --> 00:18:14,666
I mean...

421
00:18:14,750 --> 00:18:16,166
I'd really like to
work with you on this.

422
00:18:17,791 --> 00:18:19,041
That sounds like Ayako!

423
00:18:21,125 --> 00:18:22,666
-Open up! I'm trapped!
-Stand back!

424
00:18:22,750 --> 00:18:24,208
I'm gonna kick it down.

425
00:18:24,291 --> 00:18:26,000
Just hurry up and do it!

426
00:18:29,583 --> 00:18:31,375
I was looking around
the classroom...

427
00:18:31,458 --> 00:18:33,125
When suddenly the
door slammed shut.

428
00:18:33,208 --> 00:18:34,958
I tried opening it but
it wouldn't budge...

